02/04/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Former Prime Minister Tzannis Tzannetakis has died at the age of 82, media reported on Friday (April 2nd). Tzannetakis passed away in an Athens hospital on Thursday. The Tzannetakis-led coalition cabinet, composed of his conservative New Democracy party and the Greek Communist Party, ruled the country for three months in 1989, a time of political upheaval. (ANA-MPA, AP - 02/04/10)
